{"type":"message","id":"419e75ab","parentId":"d22757b5","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:30:48.503Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4og5tm1icr6p_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5351\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2881\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 093015 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to unify Phase 1 and Phase 2. I need to build a classifier that identifies invariant structure across pulse logs to test the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"tender-sable","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5351\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2881\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 093015 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to unify Phase 1 and Phase 2. I need to build a classifier that identifies invariant structure across pulse logs to test the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774359048500}}
{"type":"message","id":"fd6541d0","parentId":"419e75ab","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:30:48.505Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4og5tm1icr6p_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 092815\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best single action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE (Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec)\r\n- Key insight identified: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n- NEXT ACTION defined: Implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on pulse logs\r\n- Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThe immediate next action is to implement the TIC classifier. Let me look at what pulse logs exist and what the current state is.\r\n\r\nI should:\r\n1. Check what pulse log files exist\r\n2. Implement the TIC classifier\r\n\r\nLet me write a Python script that:\r\n1. Loads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Implements the invariant/variant classifier\r\n3. Measures classification accuracy\r\n4. Tests next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThis is the concrete next action to advance Phase 1.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight is documented, but the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment hasn't been implemented yet. I need to create the classifier that will test the hypothesis that causal structure IS invariant structure across pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `src/tic_classifier.py` - the Temporal Invariance Compression classifier that will:\r\n1. Load pulse logs from `logs/` directory\r\n2. Classify content as invariant (stable across sessions) vs variant (changes between sessions)\r\n3. Use n-gram overlap and edit distance to measure invariance\r\n4. Test next-pulse prediction from invariant features\r\n5. Output metrics against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction)\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\nCompressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nimport json\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Tuple\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nclass TICIClassifier:\r\n    \"\"\"Temporal Invariance Compression - Invariant/Variant Classifier\"\"\"\r\n    \r\n    def __init__(self, logs_dir: str = \"logs\", ngram_size: int = 3):\r\n        self.logs_dir = Path(logs_dir)\r\n        self.ngram_size = ngram_size\r\n        self.pulses = []\r\n        self.invariants = set()\r\n        self.variants = []\r\n    \r\n    def load_pulses(self) -> List[Dict]:\r\n        \"\"\"Load all pulse log files, sorted by timestamp.\"\"\"\r\n        pattern = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})_(\\d+)\\.md$\")\r\n        pulses = []\r\n        \r\n        for f in sorted(self.logs_dir.glob(\"pulse_*.md\")):\r\n            m = pattern.match(f.name)\r\n            if m:\r\n                content = f.read_text()\r\n                pulses.append({\r\n                    \"path\": f,\r\n                    \"date\": m.group(1),\r\n                    \"seq\": int(m.group(2)),\r\n                    \"content\": content,\r\n                    \"ngrams\": self._extract_ngrams(content)\r\n                })\r\n        \r\n        self.pulses = pulses\r\n        return pulses\r\n    \r\n    def _extract_ngrams(self, text: str) -> Counter:\r\n        \"\"\"Extract word n-grams from text.\"\"\"\r\n        words = re.findall(r'\\b\\w+\\b', text.lower())\r\n        ngrams = []\r\n        for i in range(len(words) - self.ngram_size + 1):\r\n            ngrams.append(tuple(words[i:i + self.ngram_size]))\r\n        return Counter(ngrams)\r\n    \r\n    def _jaccard(self, set1: set, set2: set) -> float:\r\n        \"\"\"Jaccard similarity between two sets.\"\"\"\r\n        if not set1 or not set2:\r\n            return 0.0\r\n        return len(set1 & set2) / len(set1 | set2)\r\n    \r\n    def classify_invariant_variant(self) -> Dict[str, any]:\r\n        \"\"\"Classify content as invariant (stable across sessions) or variant (changes).\"\"\"\r\n        if len(self.pulses) < 2:\r\n            return {\"invariants\": [], \"variants\": [], \"classification_rate\": 0}\r\n        \r\n        # Track n-gram frequencies across all pulses\r\n        ngram_presence = Counter()\r\n        for p in self.pulses:\r\n            for ng in p[\"ngrams\"]:\r\n                ngram_presence[ng] += 1\r\n        \r\n        total_ngrams = len(self.pulses)\r\n        \r\n        # INVARIANT: appears in >=80% of pulses\r\n        invariant_threshold = 0.8\r\n        self.invariants = {ng for ng, count in ngram_presence.items() \r\n                          if count / total_ngrams >= invariant_threshold}\r\n        \r\n        # VARIANT: appears in <50% of pulses\r\n        variant_threshold = 0.5\r\n        variants = [ng for ng, count in ngram_presence.items()\r\n                   if count / total_ngrams < variant_threshold]\r\n        \r\n        classification_rate = len(self.invariants) / max(len(ngram_presence), 1)\r\n        \r\n        return {\r\n            \"invariants\": list(self.invariants)[:100],  # sample\r\n            \"variant_count\": len(variants),\r\n            \"total_ngrams\": len(ngram_presence),\r\n            \"classification_rate\": classification_rate\r\n        }\r\n    \r\n    def predict_next_pulse(self, history: List[Dict]) -> Dict[str, float]:\r\n        \"\"\"Predict next pulse content from invariant features.\"\"\"\r\n        if len(history) < 3:\r\n            return {\"accuracy\": 0.0, \"prediction_count\": 0}\r\n        \r\n        # Build prediction model from invariants\r\n        correct = 0\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 09:28:43\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774359048503}}
